thread.title: O'Hara's Arizin sets meet record at Catholic League championships
thread.title_full: O'Hara's Arizin sets meet record at Catholic League championships

title: O'Hara's Arizin sets meet record at Catholic League championships
text:
Jack Goodwillie, Inquirer Staff Writer Posted: Sunday, October 25, 2015, 3:01 AM 
Junior Olivia Arizin of Cardinal O'Hara broke a 17-year-old meet record Saturday at the Catholic League Cross-Country Championships. 
Arizin finished the 3.1-mile Belmont Plateau course in 18 minutes, 32 seconds, breaking the mark of 18:36 set by Sheila Klick of Archbishop Prendergast in 1998. 
O'Hara's Grace Mancini, Elizabeth Mancini, and Sara Hayes finished third, fourth and fifth, respectively, to help the Lions win the Catholic League championship. In the boys' race, Cardinal O'Hara's Rob Morro finished first in 16:22 to win the individual title. His teammate Ryan James was second in 16:30. More coverage
